Package com.rb.nonbiz.testmatchers

Class Match<T,​F>

java.lang.Object
com.rb.nonbiz.testmatchers.Match<T,​F>
Type Parameters:
T - type of object whose fields we are comparing via a matcher
F - type of an object's field that's being compared
public class Match<T,​F>
extends java.lang.Object
Infrastructure to help with using TypeSafeMatcher in our tests, and thus make it easier to test (vs. have it be so difficult that developers won't bother.)

This helps avoid the mistake of having the expected and actual on both sides of a match in the (typical) static functions that return TypeSafeMatcher in a data class test that extends RBTestMatcher.
